cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.PL, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptology and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on detecting security threats in smart contracts.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper proposes a new approach to improve the safety of smart contracts.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses long-short term memory (LSTM) for sequential learning of smart contract weaknesses.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the limitations of symbolic analysis tools for smart contracts and proposes a new approach using machine learning.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also relevant as the paper uses machine learning techniques to improve the analysis of smart contracts.
